    "Active Input Rules tab info box" => "\n                List of active Input Rules.\n                <br/>In order to activate a rule, it must first be mapped to a source language.               <br/>Once the content is found in the source language <b>and</b> an active output rule for the target language is defined, it will be protected as an internal tag <b>and</b> automatically converted according to the defined output rule.\n                <br/><b>Rules with higher priorities will be applied first.</b>\n                <br/>If the desired rule is not available in the drop-down list, activate it (or add and activate it) in the “Content Recognition Rules” tab.\n                ",
