    "crossLanguageResourceSynchronization.emptyTableText" => "\nThis language resource is not yet connected to any other language resource.<br/>\nConnections are created from source language resource to target one.<br/>\nThe language resource can only be connected to another language resource if the following conditions are met:<br/>\n- Both language resources have the same language pair<br/>\n- Both language resources are assigned to the same client<br/>\n- Both language resources have data that can be synchronized, e.g: terms can be converted into a glossary<br/>\n- The target language resource is not yet linked to the other language resource (at the moment we do not support multiple sources)<br/>\nSynchronization always takes place in one direction: source data -&gt; target\n                ",
